headline: Transource and BHE Transmission to Build Nearly 200-Mile 765-kV Transmission Line in Wisconsin
summary: A joint venture between Transource Energy, LLC and BHE Transmission plans to build a nearly 200 mile, 765-kV line in Wisconsin following selection by the Midcontinent Independent System Operator (MISO).

headline: IPPs Face Competition From Distributed Power In Race To Energize Data Centers
summary: Providers of modular, behind-the-meter power generation are gaining a substantial foothold in the race to energize large load customers. Read more here.
